<body id="index">
  <span id="shroud"><div id="standoff">
    Loading...
  </div></span>
  <nav id="index-navbar">
    <div class="ripple" id="toTop">
      <i class="mdi mdi-format-vertical-align-top mdi-light mdi-24px button"></i>
    </div>
    <h3>Mordecai Stevens</h3>
    <div class="ripple" id="github">
      <i class="mdi mdi-code-tags mdi-light mdi-24px button"></i>
    </div>
    <span id="github-slider"><%= link_to("View GitHub profile", 'https://github.com/cm-s/skillsDev', :id => 'github_link') %></span>
  </nav>
  <header>
    <h1>Mordecai Stevens, Aspiring Programmer</h1>
  </header>
    <!--background illistrations here-->
    <div id="gradient-shadow"></div>
  <div id="card-stack">
    <div class="section-card" id="card-one">
      <div id="intro-container">
        <%= image_tag('core/self.png', :id => 'portrait') %>
        <p>
          Over less than a year I've became comfortable in many coding languages
        </p>
      </div>
      <div id="terminal-sect-container">
      <p id="terminal-explanation">
        <style media="screen">
          #csci-page { color: #009db9; }
        </style>
        My biggest <mark id="caveat">completed*</mark> project (in it's many versions) is called adv_game. Originally modeled after the requirements listed from <%= link_to("foobt.net", 'http://foobt.net', :id => 'csci-page') %> for a text adventure; My interpretation of such comes complete with semi-modular functionallity for easy level setup and many built in features. All this rewritten in <mark id="python">Python</mark>, <mark id="java">Java</mark>, and <mark id="cplusplus">C++</mark>.
      </p>
      <div id="console-container">
        <div id="console-navbar">
          <div class="console-navbutton" id="window-close"></div>
          <div class="console-navbutton" id="window-min"></div>
          <div class="console-navbutton" id="window-max"></div>
          <p id="console-window-title">./build.sh</p>
        </div>
        <div id="console-window">
          <p class="terminal-line">~$ cd skillsDev/learning-cpp</p>
          <p class="terminal-line">~/skillsDev/learning-cpp$ cd CSCI_PP4_JAVA</p>
          <p class="terminal-line">~/skillsDev/learning-cpp/CSCI_PP4_JAVA$ ./build.sh</p>
          <p class="terminal-line">building adv_game...</p>
          <p class="terminal-line">Times ran since v.1.9.5: 188</p>
          <p class="terminal-line">******************************************</p>
          <pre class="terminal-line">*                Main Menu               *</pre>
          <pre class="terminal-line">*         Type anything to start         *</pre>
          <pre class="terminal-line">*        Type "stats" for statistics     *</pre>
          <pre class="terminal-line">*          Type "help" for help          *</pre>
          <p class="terminal-line">******************************************</p>
          <div id="terminal-last-line">
            <p id="terminal-last-text">>></p>
            <div id="cursor"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      </div>
      <div id="card-one-footer">All I've written is generated by myself without any reference to others' work unless explicitly denoted.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="section-card" id="card-two">
      <h4>Internal Links</h4>
      <div id="site-ext-container">
        <div class="topic-container">
          <span class="topic-title" id="mm-title">
            Material Messenger
          </span>
          <div class="canvas">
          <!-- chat bubble one -->
            <div class="background-top" id="mm-icon-left">
                <div class="mm-icon-text-line"></div>
                <div class="mm-icon-text-line"></div>
                <div class="mm-icon-text-line"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="background-bottom" id="mm-icon-left-bottom">
                <div id="blue-cutoff-left"></div>
            </div>
          <!-- chat bubble two -->
            <div class="background-top" id="mm-icon-right">
              <div class="mm-icon-text-line"></div>
              <div class="mm-icon-text-line"></div>
              <div class="mm-icon-text-line"></div>
            </div>
            <div class="background-bottom" id="mm-icon-right-bottom">
              <div id="blue-cutoff-right"></div>
            </div>
            <%= react_component('MmBubble', props = { size: 50, top: 155, left: 235, interval: 3800 }, html_options = { prerender: false }) %>
            <%= react_component('MmBubble', props = { size: 40, top: 20, left: 30, interval: 4800 }, html_options = { prerender: false }) %>
            <%= react_component('MmBubble', props = { size: 120, top: -23, left: 147, interval: 5000 }, html_options = { prerender: false }) %>
            <%= react_component('MmBubble', props = { size: 85, top: -27, left: 66, interval: 3400 }, html_options = { prerender: false }) %>
            <%= react_component('MmBubble', props = { size: 95, top: 60, left: 20, interval: 4400 }, html_options = { prerender: false }) %>
          </div>
          <%= react_component('WideButton', props={href: 'core/getmessenger', margin: '0', background: '#2998ff', text: 'Goto Messenger', width: 140}, html_options={prerender: false}) %>
        </div>
        <div class="topic-container">
          <span class="topic-title" id="projects-title">Projects</span>
          <div class="canvas">

          </div>
          <%= react_component('WideButton', props={href: 'core/extras', margin: '0', background: '#ffc966', text: 'Check it Out', width: 110}, html_options={prerender: false}) %>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div id="site-ext-info-container">
        <div class="site-topic-info-sect">
          <em>What is Material Messenger?</em>
          <p>
            Material Messenger is an immitation messaging application, modeled after Facebook's Messenger and more specifically the basic functions of .
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="site-topic-info-sect">
          <em>More on these projects</em>
          <p>
            The link above is to an index of all the small projects that I have made.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="section-card" id="card-three">
      <%= react_component('AboutMeSection', html_options = {prerender: true}, props = {  }) %>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
